        <num>CE 603</num>
        <heading>603.  Oath or affirmation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 603.  Oath or affirmation
Before testifying, every witness shall be required to declare that he will testify truthfully, by oath or affirmation administered in a form calculated to awaken his conscience and impress his mind with his duty to do so.</p>
        </content>
